                  <summary>I) Maṣḥafa  gәṣṣәw, Lectionary for the week (fols. 2ra-36ra)&#xD;
- Blessing prayer (Barәkännä ʾәgziʾo… “Bless us, Lord…”: fols. 2ra-4rb&#xD;
- Monday (sänuy): fols. 5ra-9ra&#xD;
- Tuesday (śälus): fols. 9rb-15rb&#xD;
- Thursday (ḥamus): fols. 15rb-19va&#xD;
- Friday (ʾarb): fols. 19va-24vb&#xD;
- Saturday (qädamit): fols. 24vb-29vb&#xD;
- Sunday (ʾǝḥud): fols. 30ra-36ra&#xD;
II) Maṣḥafa  nәfq “Book of the Assistant Priest” (fols. 36ra-48rb)&#xD;
I-1) Prayer of oblation (fols. 36ra-37ra): excerpt from the Liturgy of Catechumen (MQ, Śәrʿatä qәddase, ch. III, §§ 41-44). &#xD;
I-2) Fәtḥat zä-wald “Absolution of the Son” (fols. 37ra-39rb): excerpt from the Liturgy of Catechumen (MQ, Śәrʿatä qәddase, ch. III, §§ 56-65).&#xD;
I-3) Concluding chant after the reading from the Pauline Epistles (fols. 39rb-40rb): excerpt from the Liturgy of the Word (MQ, Śәrʿatä qәddase, ch. III, §§ 132-135).&#xD;
I-4) Universal prayer by the assistant priest (fols. 40rb-42ra): excerpt from the Liturgy of the Word (MQ, Śәrʿatä qәddase, ch. III, §§ 194-209).&#xD;
I-5) Supplication for peace, the hierarchy and the assembly (fols. 42ra-43ra): excerpt from the Liturgy of the Word (MQ, Śәrʿatä qәddase, ch. IV, §§ 15-21).&#xD;
I-6) Prayer of blessing of St. Basil (fols. 43ra-44vb): excerpt from the Liturgy of the Eucharist, Anaphora of the Apostles (MQ, Qәddase zä-ḥawaryat, §§ 10-21).&#xD;
I-7) Prayer of intercession following the imposition of the celebrant‘s hand (fols. 44vb-48rb): excerpt from the Liturgy of the Eucharist, Anaphora of the Apostles (MQ, Qәddase zä-ḥawaryat, §§ 154-158)&#xD;
&#xD;
Additio 1.</summary>
